

Deborah "Debbie" Ann Harry (born Angela Trimble; July 1, 1945) is an American singer, songwriter, and actress, known as the lead vocalist of the band Blondie. Her recordings with the band reached No.â€Š1 in the US and UK charts on many occasions from 1979 to 2017.Born in Miami, Florida, Harry was adopted as an infant and raised in Hawthorne, New Jersey. After attending college, she worked various jobs, including as a secretary (including at the BBC in New York), dancer, and Playboy Bunny, before breaking through in the music industry. Harry co-formed Blondie in 1974 in New York City. 
